\v 16 And he divided\f + \ft Q, Impf., hxj\f* the three hundred men into three companies and he gave horns and empty jars in the hand of all of them and there were torches in the midst of the jars.
\v 17 And he said to them “From me you shall see and so you shall do, and behold I am coming to the edge of the camp and as I do so you shall do.
\v 18 And I shall blow the horn, I and all who are with me, you shall blow the horns as you are around all the camp and you shall say, ‘For the Lord and for Gideon.’”
